main event: Multiple witnesses reported a silvery, disc-shaped object in the sky near Tillamook, Oregon on January 24, 1949, at different times of the day.
interesting points: One witness reported seeing a silvery object in the sky that seemed to have no distinct shape and was about the size of the full moon.
Another witness described the object as round and silvery, and was unable to determine whether it was moving.
The reported speed of the object varied among witnesses, with estimates ranging from 30-35 miles per hour to 400-450 miles per hour.
One witness noted that the object seemed to float without making any sound or leaving a trail.
The weather conditions at the time of the sightings were described as pleasant, clear, with no ground haze or clouds.
sighted object: silvery, disc-shaped object in the sky
photographs: No photographs included in the report
